{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "af8af87c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Quickly apply gravity loads and obtain mass and stiffness matrices"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9f5894fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This document mainly introduces some model data retrieval methods in opstool."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "51923ded",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import openseespy.opensees as ops\n",
    "\n",
    "import opstool as opst\n",
    "import opstool.vis.pyvista as opsvis\n",
    "\n",
    "opsvis.set_plot_props(notebook=True)  # set notebook mode, you can set it to False for a practical use"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9c244a6d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8a439d82",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will use two methods to add mass to the model: one is to specify the mass of the nodes using `mass`, and the other is to specify the linear density (`-mass`) when creating beam elements."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "caf2f69c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.wipe()\n",
    "ops.model(\"basic\", \"-ndm\", 2, \"-ndf\", 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the model nodes\n",
    "ops.node(1, 0.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.node(2, 2.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.node(3, 0.0, 2.0)\n",
    "ops.node(4, 0.0, 2.0)\n",
    "ops.node(5, 2.0, 2.0)\n",
    "ops.node(6, 2.0, 2.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Constrain the nodes\n",
    "ops.rigidLink(\"beam\", 3, 4)  # Rigid link between nodes 3 and 4\n",
    "ops.equalDOF(5, 6, 1, 2, 3)  # Equal DOF between nodes 5 and 6\n",
    "\n",
    "ops.fix(1, 1, 1, 1)\n",
    "ops.fix(2, 1, 1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assign the node masses\n",
    "ops.mass(1, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(2, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(3, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(4, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(5, 10.0, 10.0, 1e-3)\n",
    "ops.mass(6, 10.0, 10.0, 1e-3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the elements\n",
    "ops.geomTransf(\"Linear\", 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# element('elasticBeamColumn', eleTag, *eleNodes, Area, E_mod, Iz, transfTag, <'-mass', mass>)\n",
    "Area, E_mod, Iz = 1.0, 1.0, 1.0\n",
    "ops.element(\"elasticBeamColumn\", 1, 1, 3, Area, E_mod, Iz, 1, \"-mass\", 1.0)\n",
    "ops.element(\"elasticBeamColumn\", 2, 2, 5, Area, E_mod, Iz, 1, \"-mass\", 1.0)\n",
    "ops.element(\"elasticBeamColumn\", 3, 4, 6, Area, E_mod, Iz, 1, \"-mass\", 1.0)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "cd5bc2fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = opsvis.plot_model(show_node_numbering=True, show_ele_numbering=True)\n",
    "fig.show(jupyter_backend=\"static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f94106a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Apply the gravity load"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "802ad99f",
   "metadata": {
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "The opstool utility provides a function :func:`opstool.pre.create_gravity_load` to quickly apply gravity loads. \n",
    "**This function internally retrieves all masses in the model, including those defined at nodes, in elements, and in materials.** \n",
    "You only need to provide the multiplier (gravitational acceleration) and the direction of load application."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "c32f6d14",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ops.timeSeries(\"Constant\", 1)  # Define a constant time series, tag = 1\n",
    "ops.pattern(\"Plain\", 1, 1)  # Define a load pattern, tag = 1\n",
    "node_loads = opst.pre.create_gravity_load(direction=\"Y\", factor=-9.81)  # Create gravity loads in the pattern tag=1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "06ea3642",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A internally calls the ``load`` command to add node loads and also returns a dictionary of load values:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "6d28b09a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Node Loads:\n",
      "Node 1: [0.0, -19.62, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 2: [0.0, -19.62, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 3: [0.0, -19.62, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 4: [0.0, -19.62, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 5: [0.0, -107.91000000000001, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 6: [0.0, -107.91000000000001, 0.0]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Node Loads:\")\n",
    "for node, load in node_loads.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"Node {node}: {load}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "893ab59e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " Therefore, you can easily create gravity loads directly through the above commands. \n",
    "The way you specify the mass when modeling is arbitrary. \n",
    "opstool can help you do all the internal conversions!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9073b318",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###  Get Model Mass"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9c1c1739",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "``get_node_mass`` returns a dictionary containing all masses defined in the model, both at nodes and elements."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "b518b56b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "node_mass = opst.pre.get_node_mass()  # get the node mass dict"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "79719a7c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Node Masses:\n",
      "Node 1: [2.0, 2.0, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 2: [2.0, 2.0, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 3: [2.0, 2.0, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 4: [2.0, 2.0, 0.0]\n",
      "Node 5: [11.0, 11.0, 0.001]\n",
      "Node 6: [11.0, 11.0, 0.001]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Node Masses:\")\n",
    "for node, mass in node_mass.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"Node {node}: {mass}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3b2503b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "  \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    " First, part of it comes from\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "ops.mass(1, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(2, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(3, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(4, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "ops.mass(5, 10.0, 10.0, 1e-3)\n",
    "ops.mass(6, 10.0, 10.0, 1e-3)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    " The second comes from the beam elements:\n",
    "\n",
    "``length = 2, density = 1.0, area = 1.0``\n",
    "\n",
    "The mass assigned to each node is:\n",
    "\n",
    "``length * density * area / 2 = 1.0``\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, the returned mass is completely accurate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "54446546",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In practice, ``create_gravity_load`` calls ``get_node_mass`` to iteratively create nodal loads internally."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bd89a29c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Get system matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fa20917a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You can get the mass, stiffness and damping matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b9eb430d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Get Matrix from Penalty-constraint method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "3c6ea432",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "constraints_args = [\"Penalty\", 1e10, 1e10]  # This affects the dimensions of the matrix\n",
    "system_args = [\"FullGeneral\"]  # Full matrix system must be used\n",
    "numberer_args = [\"RCM\"]  # It affects the topology of the matrix and the order of dof."
   ]

      "         0.e+00,  0.e+00,  0.e+00,  0.e+00, -1.e+10,  0.e+00,  0.e+00,\n",
      "         1.e+10,  0.e+00,  0.e+00,  0.e+00],\n",

   "source": [
    "M = opst.pre.get_mck(\"m\", constraints_args=constraints_args, system_args=system_args, numberer_args=numberer_args)\n",

  {

   "source": [

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fe01ee53",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "####  Get Matrix from Transformation-constraint approach"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "20d5e5a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "constraints_args = [\"Transformation\"]  # This affects the dimensions of the matrix\n",
    "system_args = [\"FullGeneral\"]  # Full matrix system must be used\n",
    "numberer_args = [\"Plain\"]  # It affects the topology of the matrix and the order of dof."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "83f8a268",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Stiffness Matrix (K):\n",

      " [ 1.5  1.5  4.   0.  -1.5  1. ]\n",

    "nodeTagsDofs1 = K.coords[\"nodeTagsDofs-1\"].values  # \"nodeTag-Dof\" coordinate\n",
    "nodeTagsDofs2 = K.coords[\"nodeTagsDofs-2\"].values\n",
    "K = K.values\n",
    "print(\"Stiffness Matrix (K):\")\n",
    "print(K)"
   ]

   ]
